b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Machida vs. Anders</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 125</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event produced by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> held on February 3, 2018, at Arena Guilherme Paraense in <a href="/wiki/Bel%C3%A9m" title="Bel\xc3\xa9m">Bel\xc3\xa9m</a>, Brazil.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-BelemFN_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-BelemFN-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>While the UFC has hosted several events in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Northeast_Brazil" title="Northeast Brazil">Northeast Brazil</a>, the event marked the promotion\'s first visit to <a href="/wiki/Par%C3%A1" title="Par\xc3\xa1">Par\xc3\xa1</a> in the country\'s <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Northern_Brazil" title="Northern Brazil">North region</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-BelemFN_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-BelemFN-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A middleweight bout between former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Light_Heavyweight_Championship" title="UFC Light Heavyweight Championship">UFC Light Heavyweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Lyoto_Machida" title="Lyoto Machida">Lyoto Machida</a> and <a href="/wiki/Eryk_Anders" title="Eryk Anders">Eryk Anders</a> headlined this event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-headliner_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-headliner-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Luis_Henrique_(fighter)" title="Luis Henrique (fighter)">Luis Henrique</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Timothy_Johnson_(fighter)" title="Timothy Johnson (fighter)">Timothy Johnson</a> at the event. However, Henrique was removed from the pairing in early December and was replaced by Marcelo Golm.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-HenriqueOut_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-HenriqueOut-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>At the weigh-ins <a href="/wiki/Michel_Prazeres" title="Michel Prazeres">Michel Prazeres</a> weighed in at 161 pounds, 5 pounds over the lightweight non title fight upper limit of 156 pounds. As a result, the bout proceeded at catchweight and Prazeres was expected to be fined 20% of his purse which will go to his opponent <a href="/wiki/Desmond_Green" title="Desmond Green">Desmond Green</a>. If he wins, he also would forfeit 20 percent of his win bonus.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Pedro_Munhoz" title="Pedro Munhoz">Pedro Munhoz</a> also missed weight, 4 pounds over the bantamweight non title fight upper limit of 136 pounds. In turn, his bout against former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Flyweight_Championship" title="UFC Flyweight Championship">UFC Flyweight Championship</a> challenger and <a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter:_Team_Bisping_vs._Team_Miller" title="The Ultimate Fighter: Team Bisping vs. Team Miller">The Ultimate Fighter: Team Bisping vs. Team Miller</a> bantamweight winner <a href="/wiki/John_Dodson_(fighter)" title="John Dodson (fighter)">John Dodson</a> was pulled from the card after Dodson declined to take the fight.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup> Meanwhile, Prazeres was supposed to weigh a maximum of 173 pounds on the night of the event for the fight to proceed as scheduled, but according to Green\'s camp, Prazeres weighed in at 180 pounds. Despite that, Green still accepted the fight and Prazeres gave him 40% of his purse.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>]'